SALT LAKE CITY — Javelin Guidry made quite an impression at the NFL Scouting Combine.
He’s got a ton of speed,” said Utah defensive coordinator Morgan Scalley.
He’s also extremely tough and has for us played that nickel position extremely well.”In 41 games at Utah, Guidry tallied 120 tackles (82 solo) with 19 passes defended and three interceptions.
I’m ready to do that at the next level.” — Javelin Guidry“I wanted to be the fastest one there,” Guidry said.
